latestIgtvVideos.title: Frida Kahlo, the ultimate inspiration 😍
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Why is Frida Kahlo is such an inspiration, especially today? Because she turned her pain into art. ✨🌷

A look at the spirit and determination with which Frida Kahlo expressed her life’s situations through art and, in turn, created beauty for the world. Just the motivation we need today…

✨

Frida was a woman of strength and spirit. Brave, determined, and most of all, beautiful. 

✨

In order of appearance:

Photograph of Frida Kahlo
Self-Portrait with Thorn Necklace and Hummingbird, 1940, @ransomcenter

The Bus, 1929
Photographs of the specially-designed easel 

Self Portrait - Time Flies, 1939 
Self-Portrait with Monkey and Parrot, 1942

Frida Kahlo and Diego Rivera, San Francisco, California

The Frame, 1938, @museelouvre

Frida Kahlo With Magenta Rebozo, photographed by Nickolas Muray, 1939

latestIgtvVideos.title: The Most Fashionable Paintings in Art!💃🏻💄⭐️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Much before #OOTD came into existence, some of the world’s biggest artists were creating style with their paintings! 😍 Here are three of them—Gustave Klimt, Henri Matisse, and Amrita She-Gil and their runway-esque artworks that are simply stunning. ❤️❤️

Paintings in order of appearance:

Detail from Edwin Antonio, #vincentvangogh x Venus in @Versace x Edwin @edwinantonioofficial @metmuseum
Untitled, Amrita Sher-Gil, 1933 @sothebys
Photograph of Gustav Klimt
Photograph of Henri Matisse

The Kiss, Gustav Klimt, 1907-08
Portrait of a Lady, Gustav Klimt, 1917 @galleriariccioddi
Portrait Of Eugenia Primavesi, Gustav Klimt, 1913 
Detail of Judith and the Head of Holofernes, Gustav Klimt, 1901

latestPosts.caption:
I had the absolute pleasure of meeting Mr Tommy Hilfiger in Mumbai recently, on a moonlit night at a private dinner against the imposing Taj Mahal Palace in Mumbai. ❤️

It was a night of dreams.

Of Mr Hilfiger’s dream, from the time when he came to Mumbai as a young man with few means but a grand vision. Today, he’s hosting his own ‘yacht’ dinner at the Taj (listen to his speech in this post).

And then, there’s the dream that 12-year-old me would have never imagined while wearing her Tommy Hilfiger shoes in black and brown when stepping out for a party.

Such a lovely gathering it was, and the cherry on top was @kaustav.dey — ever a gracious host and ever so stylish.

Welcome back to India, Mr Hilfiger 💙🤍

#TommyHilfiger #Mumbai

latestPosts.caption:
I had the absolute privilege of being invited by @astaguru @showkeen_official for a panel discussion with such brilliant minds on ‘Art For All’. 

And what a riveting conversation it was.

We all had such diverse backgrounds and points of view on art—from journalism to infrastructure and community building for up and coming artists and those who appreciate it. 

The arts needs all the impetus and support to sustain in such fragile times, for art nurtures the soul. It provides intellectual relief, it allows the inner mind to explore. But, most of all, it just makes you feel good. 

That is why art must be for all.

Thank you @jaymindalal and @rheajac for this wonderful evening.

#Astaguru #art #ShowKeen
